  <section id="outcomes">
    <div class="cgw-container">
      <p class="cgw-section-label fade-in">Why this matters</p>
      <h2 class="section-title fade-in">Word is where Copilot becomes usable business output</h2>
      <p class="section-intro fade-in">Copilot can help accelerate the most common document jobs: getting past the blank page, improving rough drafts, summarizing source material, converting notes into structured content, and turning role-specific expertise into repeatable templates.</p>
      <div class="grid-3">
        <article class="card fade-in">
          <div class="card-icon">✍️</div>
          <h3>Create faster first drafts</h3>
          <p>Start with outlines, memos, briefs, SOPs, FAQs, reports, policies, or executive summaries grounded in selected sources.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card fade-in">
          <div class="card-icon">🛠️</div>
          <h3>Improve existing writing</h3>
          <p>Rewrite selected content for clarity, brevity, tone, structure, audience fit, and table-based readability.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card fade-in">
          <div class="card-icon">🔎</div>
          <h3>Analyze before editing</h3>
          <p>Use chat-only mode to identify gaps, risks, unsupported claims, decisions needed, and assumptions before changing the file.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
      <div class="callout warning fade-in">
        <strong>Responsible use:</strong> Copilot output is a draft. Users remain accountable for final facts, numbers, legal meaning, policy interpretation, customer commitments, and approval workflows.
